It is grown from seed sown just after the autumnal equinox; if it is for the purpose of chives, it must be sown rather thickly. It goes on being cut in the same bed till it gives out; and if it is being grown to make heads it is always well manured before it is cut. then it is fully grown, it is moved to another bed. after having the points of the leaves above the central part carefully trimmed off and the tips of the coats drawn back from the heads.
